# Phone Bridge runtime "want list".
#
# Compile to requirements.txt (lockfile) with:
#   python -m piptools compile --output-file requirements.txt --strip-extras requirements.in
#
# Policy:
#   - Use `==` for things we deliberately want pinned (matches current prod, or
#     a known-good version we explicitly chose).
#   - Use `>=` for things we're willing to track latest-compatible at recompile time.
#   - During refactor phases (see CLAUDE.md §Refactor period rules) we pin
#     anything that drifted from prod, so Phase boundaries don't quietly ship a
#     dep upgrade alongside the refactor.

